title: Videographer
description: I set up and ran an in-house media department for internal video communications. The highlights include helping to create and distribute various monthly video briefings for over 5500 staff. In 2011, I also worked to produced a safety e-learning package that has gone on to become a success and is looking to be rolled out at other sites around the world. I filmed and edited interviews, internal TV shows, live events, multi-camera shoots of staff briefing sessions among many other types of videos. Over my time at Nissan, I have also provided media support for Nissan Global offices in Japan, US, Mexico, Portugal, France, Russia and Spain. I also provided support for other global internal events as well international motor shows such as Tokyo, Berlin and Geneva. I also covered events in Frankfurt, Brussels and London for Nissan Europe, including filming at Downing Street in 2011. Over my time at Nissan, I was responsible for the technical specification and implementation of all video equipment at the Nissan plant as part of the on going department development. My main task was to project manage the production and post production process on all video related activity around the plant. I researched and developed business relationships with external media suppliers as well as also working hard to set up work experience opportunities for local media students.
name: Chris Greenwood
